The paper discusses optimal pricing schemes for social goods, which involves externalities and maximizing revenue. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT), Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Economics and Computation (cs.EC), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. However, since the focus is on pricing and revenue maximization, Game Theory and Economics and Computation are the most likely sub-categories. Multi-Agent Systems and Social and Information Networks are also relevant due to the consideration of externalities, while Machine Learning may be less likely as it is not directly mentioned in the abstract.
